<br>
So, I guess what it comes down to is, does anyone have any suggestions for gauging the necessity of a 'dot spell.  Who needs them in a group, generally, and who doesn't?  Does this change by type of fight?  What is etiquette in terms of recouping reagent costs?  (For example, if I use a Peridot on everyone in the group in a LDoN adventure, my net monetary gain at the end won't be more than a few plat, most of the time.)<br>
<br>
I don't want to be a rude bitch, but neither do I want to be poverty stricken until I can hunt where loot is worth a bit more.  (Because I'm certainly not seeing a bigger split than 60 plat or so at the end of LDoN right now.)<br>
<br>
Thoughts?<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Brora Silvereyes</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
