<br>
After that, you can probably get by with sticking to jasper symbol.  Nice thing about temperence though is it lasts through a whole dungeon in LDoN - 100 minutes duration - so no worry about rebuffing midway.  If you symbol you'll be doing rebuffs half way through which may or may not be a mana issue.<br>
<br>
I'm thinking about asking my group what they prefer.  At the beginning saying that I can temp everyone but then I need 66p off the top before split to cover the peridots or we can go with cheaper buffs.  I think in the 40s a lot of people have no idea that our buffs jump from costing 8g to 10.5p and if they realize they'll either help pay for it or happily do without.<br>
<br>
Just got temp yesterday as well so struggling with the same issue.  Last time I was this level I just kept using jaspers and didn't bother even buying peris till I got older.  If you are xp grinding somewhere, not everyone needs a symbol.  If you are going for something dangerous though it can give you extra time to react and get that heal off if you gave it to them.   <p>[65 Archon] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231627">Ariene</a> (High Elf) Bristlebane<BR>
