<br>
This may not work well for you if you find yourself needing to med a lot, but I've started master looting a lot so that its easy to take off the cost of the dots for myself before splitting. <br>
<br>
But as to who you should expend the dots on... your priorities should be on main tank, enchanter, and yourself (in case you get healing aggro). In my opinion, classes like magicians and wizards and such should be able to control their aggro enough that they aren't getting hit much, so they're last on my list. Anyone who hands me a dot or some platinum I will also buff, even if I don't think they need it. As far as situation, if you're fighting things with a low chance of adds and/or weak hitting mobs, the necessity of a dot buff is less.<br>
<br>
 I think what Destrea suggested you say is a good way to go about making sure you don't have to eat the cost for all the dots you use. Oh! And try to get a reagent conservation item, if you can. Something like a Savant's Cap isn't very expensive and over time you'll save a lot of money.<br>
